  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Ngozi smallholder farmers through a sustainable Horticulture value chain</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The positive change which will happen as results of Good nutritional behavior (integrating legumes and fruits  in their  diet of smallholders farmers) trough nutritional education,  adoption of new agricultural techniques of horticulture garden market to increase their revenue. This will permit them to  adopt a balanced and diversified diet  through increased income, and then improved food security and nutrition</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intends to  focus on gender  to develop a deeper understanding of the local context, engaging a wider range of powerful actors, providing better support for women&#x2019;s mobilization and, importantly, taking a closer look at gendered power relations within Christian Aid organization to enhance horticulture garden market productivity to improve food security and nutrition. So, in this project every association will count at least 60 % of members must be women.  We know women intervene actively  in agricultural activities, to change the nutritional behavior, we must focus on women because they are the basis of kitchen activities and then, they  influence nutrition status.  This project will achieve the inclusive and sustainable growth of horticultural market gardening. So, it will allow to smallholder farmers  to access the niche market and then they will increase their income.</narrative>
  </description>
